e=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 05, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104sua1665702566764.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sua1665702566764.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sua1665702566764.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"sua1665702566764\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Attributes in Uniface XML Streams\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface uses attributes in XML streams to store data processing information and to define custom attributes.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sua1665702566764__section_w6595ab1b5b1_w6596ab1b5_w6597ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sua1665702566764__section_w6598ab1b5b3_w6599ab1b5_w6600ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d128749e56\">\n                        \n Uniface-Generated Attributes\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sua1665702566764__p_d38537e1_d38538e1_d38539e1\">Uniface automatically generates data processing attributes if they are specified in the DTD used by the stream. Most of these attributes are only valid for the XML <code class=\"ph codeph\">entity</code> elements that map to Uniface entity occurrences. XML streams can be used without these attributes, but they are required by the reconnect process (started by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">reconnect</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">retrieve/reconnect</span>), which resolves the origin and state of occurrences before they can be merged with database data.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sua1665702566764__p_d38540e1_d38541e1_d38542e1\">The valerr attribute can be applied to both the <code class=\"ph codeph\">entity</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">field</code> XML elements that map to Uniface entities and fields. It is required for remote data validation.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"sua1665702566764__table_d3821e1_d3822e1_d3823e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Uniface-Generated Attributes in XML Streams</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"sua1665702566764__table_d3821e1_d3822e1_d3823e1__entry__1\">\n Attribute\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"sua1665702566764__table_d3821e1_d3822e1_d3823e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sua1665702566764__table_d3821e1_d3822e1_d3823e1__entry__1\">\n                                id\n                              </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sua1665702566764__table_d3821e1_d3822e1_d3823e1__entry__2\">\n Uniface-generated occurrence identifier\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sua1665702566764__table_d3821e1_d3822e1_d3823e1__entry__1\">\n                                crc\n                              </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sua1665702566764__table_d3821e1_d3822e1_d3823e1__entry__2\">\n CRC checksum of the occurrence.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sua1665702566764__table_d3821e1_d3822e1_d3823e1__entry__1\">\n                                status\n                              </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sua1665702566764__table_d3821e1_d3822e1_d3823e1__entry__2\">Modification status of the occurrence:\n                              <p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">est</code> (exists in DB)</p><p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">mod</code>\n                           (modified)</p><p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">new</code> (new)</p><p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">del</code>\n                           (delete)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sua1665702566764__table_d3821e1_d3822e1_d3823e1__entry__1\">\n                                valerr\n                              </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sua1665702566764__table_d3821e1_d3822e1_d3823e1__entry__2\">\n Uniface or user-defined validation error message\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sua1665702566764__p_d38543e1_d38544e1_d38545e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dvf1665702566367.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dvf1665702566367.html#dvf1665702566367__topic_d28412e1_d28413e1_d28414e1_d28415e1_d28416e1\">Metadata for Reconnect</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sua1665702566764__section_w6601ab1b5b5_w6602ab1b5_w6603ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d128749e171\">\n                        \n User-Defined Attributes\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sua1665702566764__p_d38549e1_d38550e1_d38551e1\">You can define your own attributes by declaring them in the DTD for the XML stream. Uniface supports <code class=\"ph codeph\">FIXED</code> attributes, that is, attributes with a fixed value.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aqs1665702566840.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface-Compliant Attribute Declarations</a><p>Uniface supports a subset of the attribute declarations that are available in the XML standard, namely declarations for attributes for processing information, and declarations for namespaces.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532172\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532172\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Attributes in Uniface XML Streams Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 05, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Attributes in Uniface XML Streams Uniface uses attributes in XML streams to store data processing information and to define custom attributes. Uniface-Generated Attributes Uniface automatically generates data processing attributes if they are specified in the DTD used by the stream. Most of these attributes are only valid for the XML entity elements that map to Uniface entity occurrences. XML streams can be used without these attributes, but they are required by the reconnect process (started by reconnect and retrieve/reconnect ), which resolves the origin and state of occurrences before they can be merged with database data. The valerr attribute can be applied to both the entity and field XML elements that map to Uniface entities and fields. It is required for remote data validation. Table 1. Uniface-Generated Attributes in XML Streams Attribute Description id Uniface-generated occurrence identifier crc CRC checksum of the occurrence. status Modification status of the occurrence: est (exists in DB) mod (modified) new (new) del (delete) valerr Uniface or user-defined validation error message For more information, see Metadata for Reconnect . User-Defined Attributes You can define your own attributes by declaring them in the DTD for the XML stream. Uniface supports FIXED attributes, that is, attributes with a fixed value. Related Links Uniface-Compliant Attribute Declarations Uniface supports a subset of the attribute declarations that are available in the XML standard, namely declarations for attributes for processing information, and declarations for namespaces. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}